datasets.name: a5827d89
datasets.query:
SELECT 
    run_timestamp,
    warehouse_id,
    query_start_time_ms, query_end_time_ms,
    id,
    query_text,
    query_id as statement_id,
    concurrency, 
    benchmark_catalog, 
    benchmark_schema,   
    warehouse_name,
    duration,
    duration/1000 as duration_secs,
    -- metrics.planning_time_ms/1000 as query_planning_time_secs,
    metrics.execution_time_ms/1000 as query_execution_time_secs,
    metrics.compilation_time_ms/1000 as query_compliation_time_secs,
    metrics.result_from_cache as result_from_cache,
    metrics.rows_produced_count as rows_produced_count,
    metrics.read_files_count as read_files_count,
    metrics.read_partitions_count as read_partitions_count,
    metrics.pruned_bytes as pruned_bytes,
    metrics.pruned_files_count as pruned_files_count,
    metrics.spill_to_disk_bytes as spill_to_disk_bytes,
    metrics.rows_read_count as rows_read_count
FROM CATALOG_NAME.SCHEMA_NAME.TABLE_NAME;

datasets.name: 17c1da0b
datasets.query:
WITH Percentiles_CTE AS (
    SELECT 
        run_timestamp, 
        id, 
        warehouse_name,
        concurrency,
        transform(
            percentile_cont(array(0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 0.90, 0.99)) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY round(duration/1000, 4)), 
            x -> round(x, 4)
        ) as Percentiles, 
        min(duration)/1000 as min_duration_secs,
        median(duration)/1000 as median_duration_secs,
        round(avg(duration)/1000,4) as avg_duration_secs,
        max(duration)/1000 as max_duration_secs,
        -- round(avg(metrics.planning_time_ms)/1000,4) as avg_query_planning_time_secs,
        round(avg(metrics.execution_time_ms)/100,4) as avg_query_execution_time_secs,
        round(avg(metrics.compilation_time_ms)/1000,4) as avg_query_compliation_time_secs
    FROM CATALOG_NAME.SCHEMA_NAME.TABLE_NAME
    GROUP BY run_timestamp, id, warehouse_name, concurrency
)
SELECT 
    run_timestamp, 
    id, 
    warehouse_name,
    concurrency,
    min_duration_secs,
    median_duration_secs,
    avg_duration_secs,
    max_duration_secs,
    Percentiles[0] as P25,
    Percentiles[1] as P50,
    Percentiles[2] as P75,
    Percentiles[3] as P90,
    Percentiles[4] as P99,
    -- avg_query_planning_time_secs,
    avg_query_execution_time_secs,
    avg_query_compliation_time_secs
FROM Percentiles_CTE
ORDER BY id

datasets.name: 1a5ed835
datasets.query:
-- DO NOT USE
with dbu_size_view AS
(
  SELECT '2X-Small' AS size, 4 AS dbu_per_h
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'X-Small', 6
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'Small', 12
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'Medium', 24
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'Large', 40
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'X-Large', 80
  UNION ALL
  SELECT '2X-Large', 144
  UNION ALL
  SELECT '3X-Large', 272
  UNION ALL
  SELECT '4X-Large', 528
),

system_warehouse_cte as (
SELECT
    we.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
    we.event_type AS event,
    we.event_time AS event_time,
    we.cluster_count AS cluster_count,
    lead(event_time) over (PARTITION BY warehouse_id ORDER BY event_time) AS next_event_time
FROM
    system.compute.warehouse_events AS we
WHERE
    we.event_type IN (
        'STARTING', 'RUNNING', 'STOPPING', 'STOPPED',
        'SCALING_UP', 'SCALED_UP', 'SCALING_DOWN', 'SCALED_DOWN'
    )
    -- and warehouse_id = '8097a27ebcc78d0b'
)

select a. run_timestamp, a.benchmark_catalog, a.benchmark_schema, 
  a.warehouse_id, a.id, a.warehouse_name, a.warehouse_size, a.warehouse_type, a.duration as duration_ms,
  a.duration/(1000*60*60) as duration_hours, 
    CASE
    WHEN a.warehouse_type LIKE '%serverless%' THEN 0.7
    WHEN a.warehouse_type LIKE '%pro%' THEN 0.55
    WHEN a.warehouse_type LIKE '%classic%' THEN 0.22
  END AS unit_cost,
  b.cluster_count, c.dbu_per_h,
  duration_hours * cluster_count * c.dbu_per_h as dbus,
  dbus * unit_cost as dollar_dbus
from (
  select *, split_part(warehouse_name, " ", -1) as warehouse_size,
      split_part(warehouse_name, " ", -2) as warehouse_type
  from CATALOG_NAME.SCHEMA_NAME.TABLE_NAME
  ) a
join system_warehouse_cte b
join dbu_size_view c
on  a.warehouse_id = b.warehouse_id
and a.warehouse_size = c.size
and from_unixtime(a.query_start_time_ms/1000) between b.event_time and b.next_event_time
;

datasets.name: b5a56f81
datasets.query:
-- Statement allocated cost calculated logic is based off DBSQL Warehouse Advisor Observability Dashboard by  Databricks SQL SME group 
-- (https://github.com/CodyAustinDavis/dbsql_sme/tree/main/Observability%20Dashboards%20and%20DBA%20Resources/Observability%20Lakeview%20Dashboard%20Templates/DBSQL%20Warehouse%20Advisor%20With%20Data%20Model)
with pricing as (
    SELECT
    p.pricing.effective_list.default AS price,
    p.price_start_time,
    p.sku_name,
    p.currency_code, 
    case when p.sku_name LIKE ('%PRO%') then 'PRO' 
      WHEN p.sku_name LIKE ('%SERVERLESS%') THEN 'SERVERLESS'
      WHEN p.sku_name LIKE ('PREMIUM_SQL_COMPUTE') THEN 'CLASSIC'
    END AS warehouse_type,
    COALESCE(p.price_end_time, NOW()) AS price_end_time
  FROM
    system.billing.list_prices p
),


raw_history as (
  SELECT
    a.run_timestamp, 
    workspace_id,
    statement_id,
    compute.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
    executed_by,
    statement_text,
    a.benchmark_catalog, a.benchmark_schema, 
    a.id, a.warehouse_name, a.warehouse_size, a.warehouse_type,
    COALESCE(read_io_cache_percent, 0) AS read_io_cache_percent,
    from_result_cache,
    execution_status,
    f.statement_type,
    COALESCE(a.client_application, 'Unknown') AS client_application,
    COALESCE(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS QueryRuntimeSeconds,
    COALESCE(try_divide(total_task_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS CPUTotalExecutionTime,
    COALESCE(try_divide(execution_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS ExecutionQueryTime,
    -- Included in Cost Per Query
    COALESCE(try_divide(compilation_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS CompilationQueryTime,
    -- Included in Cost Per Query
    COALESCE(
      try_divide(waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms, 1000),
      0
    ) AS QueueQueryTime,
    COALESCE(
      try_divide(waiting_for_compute_duration_ms, 1000),
      0
    ) AS ComputeStartUpTime,
    COALESCE(try_divide(result_fetch_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS ResultFetchTime,
    -- Metric for query cost allocation - 
    CASE
      WHEN COALESCE(try_divide(total_task_duration_ms, 1000), 0) = 0 THEN 0 -- exclude metadata operations
      ELSE COALESCE(try_divide(execution_duration_ms, 1000), 0) + COALESCE(try_divide(compilation_duration_ms, 1000), 0) -- Query total time is compile time + query execution time, excluding Queue & compute start up time
    END AS TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation,
    start_time,
    end_time,
    COALESCE(total_task_duration_ms / total_duration_ms, NULL) AS TotalCPUTime_To_Execution_Time_Ratio,
    --execution time does seem to vary across query type, using total time to standardize
    COALESCE(
      waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms / total_duration_ms,
      0
    ) AS ProportionQueueTime
  FROM
    system.query.history f
  -- use left join to capture all eligible queries in case the warehouse is used by other users so the usage dbus can be properly allocated, ideally the benchmark warehouses should only be used for benchmarking purpose
  left join (
    select *, split_part(warehouse_name, " ", -1) as warehouse_size,
        split_part(warehouse_name, " ", -2) as warehouse_type
    from CATALOG_NAME.SCHEMA_NAME.TABLE_NAME
    ) a  
  where f.statement_id = a.query_id
  and compute.warehouse_id in (select distinct warehouse_id from CATALOG_NAME.SCHEMA_NAME.TABLE_NAME)
),
-- select * from raw_history

query_history_agg AS (
  SELECT
    *,
    SUM(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation) OVER (partition by warehouse_id) AS TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse,
    -- Remove listing commands in time - this are essentially "free"
    SUM(COALESCE(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation, 0)) OVER (PARTITION BY statement_text) AS TotalStatementTextTimeUsed,
    -- for query level aggregates
    try_divide(
      TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation,
      TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse
    ) AS ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery -- Remove listing commands in time - this are essentially "free"
  FROM
    raw_history
),
-- select * from query_history_agg

-- Warehouse Costs for the same query window
filtered_warehouse_usage AS (
  WITH trimmed_usage AS (
    SELECT
      usage_metadata.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
      p.warehouse_type,
      p.price as warehouse_unit_price,
      u.sku_name as sku_name,
      usage_start_time,
      usage_end_time,
      usage_quantity AS dbus
    FROM
      system.billing.usage u
      inner join pricing p 
        on p.sku_name = u.sku_name
        and u.usage_start_time between p.price_start_time and p.price_end_time
      where 
        u.usage_metadata.warehouse_id in (select distinct warehouse_id from CATALOG_NAME.SCHEMA_NAME.TABLE_NAME)
  )
  SELECT
    warehouse_id,
    warehouse_type,
    SUM(dbus ) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs,
    SUM(dbus  * warehouse_unit_price) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars
  FROM
    trimmed_usage
  GROUP BY
    all
)

SELECT
  qh.run_timestamp,
  qh.id,
  qh.workspace_id,
  qh.executed_by,
  qh.statement_id,
  qh.warehouse_id,
  qh.warehouse_name,
  u.warehouse_type,
  qh.statement_text,
  qh.QueryRuntimeSeconds,
  qh.CPUTotalExecutionTime,
  qh.ExecutionQueryTime,
  qh.CompilationQueryTime,
  qh.QueueQueryTime,
  qh.ComputeStartUpTime,
  qh.TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation,
  u.Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs,
  u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars,
  qh.ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery,
  (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) AS AllocatedQueryCostByTime,
  (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) AS AllocatedQueryDBUByTime
FROM
  query_history_agg AS qh
  LEFT JOIN filtered_warehouse_usage AS u ON u.warehouse_id = qh.warehouse_id
where
  1 = 1
  and (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) > 0
  -- only incldude queries in the benchmark
  and qh.id is not null
order by (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars :: float * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery :: float) desc
